org.acra.collector

Class CrashReportData

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.EnumMap<ReportField,Element>
        • org.acra.collector.CrashReportData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<ReportField,Element>

    public final class CrashReportData
extends java.util.EnumMap<ReportField,Element>
    Stores a crash reports data with ReportField enum values as keys.

    This is basically the source of Properties adapted to extend an EnumMap instead of Hashtable and with a few tweaks to avoid losing crazy amounts of android time in the generation of a date comment when storing to file.
